/target
/.cargo

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
Cargo.lock

# Cargo-fuzz build + corpus artefacts (the harness sources under
# `fuzz/fuzz_targets/` ARE committed; build artefacts and accumulated
# corpora / crash artefacts are not).
fuzz/target
fuzz/corpus/*/
fuzz/artifacts
